@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="catalog-section">
    <p>
        Plantry helps your household track what&rsquo;s in the pantry, plan meals, and shop smarter.
        Doing that well means holding some of your household&rsquo;s data. This page explains what we
        keep, why we keep it, and the choices you have. It is written in plain language on purpose.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">What we store</h2>
    <p>
        We store the information you and your household put into Plantry so the app can do its job:
        your account details, the household you belong to, your pantry stock, recipes, meal plans,
        shopping lists, and the receipts you scan. This data belongs to your household and is used to
        run the features you see &mdash; nothing more.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Your household&rsquo;s data stays yours</h2>
    <p>
        Every record in Plantry is scoped to a single household. Members of your household can see and
        edit your shared data; people outside it cannot. We do not sell your data, and we do not share
        it with advertisers.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Receipt scanning and AI</h2>
    <p>
        When you scan a receipt or use an AI-assisted suggestion, the relevant text is sent to an
        AI model to read the items and propose matches. You stay in control: AI results are always
        staged for your review before anything is saved to your pantry, and AI-assisted suggestions
        can be turned off in Settings. Receipt scanning uses only the content of the receipt you
        upload.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Keeping data secure</h2>
    <p>
        Access to your household&rsquo;s data requires signing in, and household isolation is enforced
        at both the application and database layers. We keep your data only as long as your account is
        active or as needed to provide the service.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="catalog-section">
    <h2 class="catalog-section__heading">Questions</h2>
    <p>
        If you have a question about your data or want it removed, reach out through your household
        account. We&rsquo;ll update this page as Plantry grows, so it always reflects how the app
        actually handles your information.
    </p>
</section>
